onal name <i>Cēola</i> (compare   Chilcott  ), or from Old English <i>ceole</i> ‘deep valley’."]}]},{"name":"Constance","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval form of the Late Latin name <i>Constantia</i>, which is either a feminine derivative of <i>Constans</i> (  see  Constant  ) or an abstract noun meaning ‘constancy’. This was a popular name among the Normans, and was borne by, amongst others, the formidable Constance of Sicily (  1158–98 ), wife of the Emperor  Henry VI ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Constance De Chelton was born in 1242, in Devon, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Robert de Chelton. She married Wimond Raleigh of Collaton about 1263, in Rayleigh, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons."},"et":{"1242–":"1242–Surnud","1242–Female":"1242–Surnud","1225–1270":"1225–1270","1234–Male":"1234–Surnud","1262–Male":"1262–Surnud","1270–1303":"1270–1303","–Male":"Surnud","1303":"1303","about 1270":"umbes 1270","1225":"1225","1234":"1234","1242":"1242","1262":"1262","1270":"1270","abt. 1262":"umbes 1262","about 1263":"umbes 1263","Rayleigh, Essex, England":"Rayleigh, Essex, England","Collaton, Raleigh, Devon, Eng.":"Rayleigh, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Smallridge, Axminster, Devon, England":"Smallridge, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1242–":"1242–Kuollut","1242–Female":"1242–Kuollut","1225–1270":"1225–1270","1234–Male":"1234–Kuollut","1262–Male":"1262–Kuollut","1270–1303":"1270–1303","–Male":"Kuollut","1303":"1303","about 1270":"noin 1270","1225":"1225","1234":"1234","1242":"1242","1262":"1262","1270":"1270","abt. 1262":"noin 1262","about 1263":"noin 1263","Rayleigh, Essex, England":"Rayleigh, Essex, England","Collaton, Raleigh, Devon, Eng.":"Rayleigh, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Smallridge, A